commit.message: Patch `.github/workflows/haskell-ci.yml` to pass cabal flag `-test-hlint`

Bump deps for GHC 9.8; Haskell CI for GHC 8.0 - 9.8.1

The hlint testsuite does not build on GHC 9.8.1 yet because of dependencies.
Allow ghc-prim-0.10 for ghc-9.6

Support GHC 9.4

Fixes #34

Signed-off-by: Elliot Marsden <elliot.marsden@gmail.com>

chore: bump ghc-prim/bytestring bounds

Fixes #31.

tests/hlint: fix when using stack, new-build, etc

The hlint test previously used a hard-coded hack to find cabal_macros.h,
so hlint could properly run over the source code. This was an old
byproduct of the testing infrastructure being born originally from
Edward Kmett.

Now, the hlint test uses filemanip to find the cabal_macros.h file
manually, so it should always Do The Right Thing, or fail.
